===Etymology===
Ancient Greek [[κινέω]] ''(cineō,'' put in motion) + [[αἴσθησις]] ''(aesthēsis,'' sensation) in form -αισθησία after [[anaesthesia]], etc.  Cf. Modern Greek [[κιναισθησία]].

===Noun===
'''kinesthesia'''
# the [[perception]] of the [[position]], [[weight]] and [[movement]] of the [[body]], its [[limb]]s and [[muscle]]s etc

